SIMPLE: corporate
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Corporate
<hw>Cor"po*rate</hw> <pr>(k?r"p?-r?t)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>corporatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>corporare</ets> to shape into a
body, fr. <ets>corpus</ets> body. See <er>Corpse</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Formed into a body by legal enactment; united in an
association, and endowed by law with the rights and liabilities of an
individual; incorporated; <as>as, a <ex>corporate</ex>
town</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Belonging to a corporation or incorporated
body.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Corporate</xex> property.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Hallam.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>United; general; collectively one.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They answer in a joint and <qex>corporate</qex> voice.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Corporate member</b></col>, <cd>an actual or voting
member of a corporation, as distinguished from an associate or an
honorary member; as, a <xex>corporate member</xex> of the American
Board.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corporate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Corporate
<hw>Cor"po*rate</hw> <pr>(-r?t)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To
incorporate.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au> Stow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corporate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Corporate
<hw>Cor"po*rate</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To become
incorporated.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corporately</ent>⟦br⟧
